# SEO & Metadata

Use App Router `metadata` / `generateMetadata` — not manual `<head>` hacks. Public content is **publish-gated**: API `getPublicBySlug` only returns `PUBLISHED`; drafts must stay noindex / unroutable.

## Pattern (already on articles)

```tsx
// apps/web/app/(gift)/articles/[slug]/page.tsx
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const article = await load(params.slug);
  if (!article) return { title: 'Article' };
  return {
    title: article.seo.title,
    description: article.seo.description ?? undefined,
    alternates: { canonical: article.seo.canonicalPath },
    openGraph: {
      title: article.seo.title,
      description: article.seo.description ?? undefined,
      images: article.seo.ogImageUrl ? [article.seo.ogImageUrl] : undefined,
    },
  };
}
```

Mirror this for PDP / specialists: title, description, canonical, OG image from **real data**.

## Rules

| Do | Don't |
|---|---|
| One `h1`; semantic `main` / `article` | Keyword-stuffed titles |
| `robots: { index: false }` on admin, drafts, previews | Index unpublished articles |
| Stable readable slugs | Invent medical claims / prices in meta |
| Propose slug + title + description when drafting a new public page | Ad-hoc conflicting `<title>` in client components |

## Structured data

Add JSON-LD (`Article`, `Product`, real `FAQPage` only) when the page has verified fields. No fake availability or star ratings.

Images: honest `alt`; see `19-images-media`.
